        <div class="problem">
            <div class="content">
                <div class="title">THE PROBLEM</div>
                <br>

                <div class="problem-one problem-wrapper">
                    <div class="problem-number">1</div>
                    <div class="problem-image problem-image-one"></div>
                    <div class="problem-description">
                        Across the world, Church attendance has been in decline. The Church once led the way, shaping societies and providing guidance, but increasingly has fallen away fromt the center of cultural consciousness.
                        <br><br>
                        Churches need to reintegrate with popular culture and the surrounding community, and bring the message of Jesus’ love back to the forefront.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="problem-two problem-wrapper">
                    <div class="problem-number">2</div>
                    <div class="problem-image problem-image-two"></div>
                    <div class="problem-description">
                        Churches are beautiful buildings, from a rich architectural tradition, and even the buildings themselves signify the power of God. Yet churches are underutilized spaces, filled during services, but too often all but empty.
                        <br><br>
                        We need to get people back into churches, to revitalize the unused space, and to  bring people and energy to the church as a whole.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="problem-three problem-wrapper">
                    <div class="problem-number">3</div>
                    <div class="problem-image problem-image-three"></div>
                    <div class="problem-description">                        
                        We can view these as problems, or we can view them as opportunities to try something new. 
                        <br><br>
                        One of the greatest impediments to establishing franchise is coming up with ideal real estate. Imagine a franchise located in a church-- a widely recognize brand, an established piece of popular culture, paired with an unparalleled space.
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>
